verbose_text: Antenatal administration of progesterone prevents sPTB in women at increased risk.1 Low concentration of salivary progesterone was found to be associated with recurrent sPTB in a retrospective cohort of women at increased risk of sPTB,2 an observation that has been supported by more recent prospectively collected data.3, 4, 5 Historically HG is more common in multiple pregnancy where progesterone concentrations are higher.
